19:59.666 --> 20:01.968
and this peckerwood's
mowing the fucking lawn?

20:02.068 --> 20:03.202
Yes, he's mowing the lawn.

20:03.370 --> 20:05.137
After he mowed
the lawn in the back,

20:05.238 --> 20:06.439
and weeded the garden,

20:06.539 --> 20:08.040
and helped me
organize Elvio's bills

20:08.174 --> 20:09.509
and build a budget.

20:09.642 --> 20:12.245
How many times have you
come by to help, huh?

20:12.379 --> 20:13.613
Where are
all his fucking friends?

20:13.713 --> 20:15.682
Because you don't care
if I lose the house

20:15.815 --> 20:16.849
or my baby starves.

20:16.983 --> 20:18.718
You just care if I fuck
another man, huh?

20:21.721 --> 20:23.456
That's where
you draw the line with my life.

20:24.691 --> 20:26.759
Who do you think you are?

20:26.926 --> 20:28.127
[baby crying]

20:29.896 --> 20:31.698
Baby needs changing.

20:31.831 --> 20:33.733
You gonna do it? I bet he would.

20:33.866 --> 20:35.234
'Cause he wants to fuck you.

20:35.368 --> 20:37.604
- He never mentioned that.
- It's what he wants.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.806
Watch close, Manuel.

20:46.513 --> 20:47.780
If he keeps
playing his cards right,

20:47.914 --> 20:50.417
he might just get the chance.

20:50.550 --> 20:52.952
Some fucking friend you are.

20:54.621 --> 20:56.723
Get off my lawn
before I call the police.

20:58.791 --> 21:00.427
Now.

21:02.028 --> 21:03.496
[baby continues crying]

21:04.864 --> 21:06.966
That's the second time
you've pointed a gun at me.

21:07.099 --> 21:08.568
Third time's gonna be the last.

21:09.569 --> 21:11.338
You're goddamn right it is.

21:12.472 --> 21:14.741
And I'll see you tomorrow, motherfucker.

21:24.050 --> 21:25.485
[engine starts]

21:26.753 --> 21:28.521
[tires screeching]

22:02.154 --> 22:03.390
[Rebecca sighs]

22:11.163 --> 22:13.366
[doorbell chiming]

22:19.606 --> 22:21.040
[Nathan]
Ah.

22:21.173 --> 22:24.844
I'd like to start out by saying
this feels inappropriate.

22:24.977 --> 22:26.278
Meeting in your residence.

22:26.413 --> 22:28.415
It is also my office.

22:28.515 --> 22:31.217
M-Tex doesn't have
an office in town?

22:31.350 --> 22:33.319
We have remote offices
that move with the rigs

22:33.453 --> 22:35.354
and satellite offices
at the man camps, but I promise,

22:35.488 --> 22:37.790
you would find those
more inappropriate.

22:39.025 --> 22:39.959
Do you want some coffee?

22:41.961 --> 22:43.095
I'm fine.

22:43.195 --> 22:46.198
So it breaks down like this:

22:46.332 --> 22:49.035
three widows, eight dependents.

22:49.168 --> 22:51.370
Youngest is three months.

22:51.504 --> 22:54.073
I was thinking something
like 250 per household,

22:54.206 --> 22:55.875
plus a college fund.

22:56.008 --> 22:58.678
Uh... M-Tex could invest
that money now

22:58.811 --> 23:00.179
and essentially pay the tuition
with the ROI,

23:00.312 --> 23:02.882
minus the three teenagers.

23:03.015 --> 23:05.217
It makes for a very attractive
and compassionate offer

23:05.351 --> 23:07.086
that addresses
the short-term needs

23:07.219 --> 23:08.988
and longer-term concerns
of the families.

23:09.088 --> 23:12.892
Are you including the cash value
of their 401(k)s in that 250?

23:13.025 --> 23:15.795
- I am not.
- So in the case of Luis,

23:15.895 --> 23:18.531
it's more like a $600,000 offer.

23:18.665 --> 23:20.767
Not really.
They're entitled to the 401(k)

23:20.900 --> 23:23.636
- regardless of a settlement.
- They don't know that.

23:23.770 --> 23:25.271
Their attorney will.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.306
- Do they have attorneys?
- Not to my knowledge.

23:27.474 --> 23:29.776
We're gonna make this deal
before they get them.

23:29.942 --> 23:31.110
Let me just check

23:31.277 --> 23:32.512
- with the insurance company's--
- Don't you dare.

23:33.946 --> 23:36.549
The insurance company isn't
gonna offer them anything.

23:36.649 --> 23:38.818
They're going to investigate
for a year,

23:38.985 --> 23:41.488
claim it was negligence
on the part of the employees

23:41.621 --> 23:42.955
and then wash their hands of it.

23:43.089 --> 23:44.991
There is no cap

23:45.124 --> 23:48.795
for economic or punitive damages
for wrongful death in Texas.

23:48.928 --> 23:51.564
And this is a $40
or $50 million dollar lawsuit.

23:51.664 --> 23:53.132
Per incident.

23:53.265 --> 23:54.801
We won't let it get that far.

23:54.934 --> 23:57.303
If they don't bite at 250,
we will offer 300.

23:57.470 --> 23:59.472
If they don't bite there, 400.

23:59.639 --> 24:00.940
And if they still don't bite,

24:01.073 --> 24:03.242
I scare the shit out of them
for an hour,

24:03.342 --> 24:04.711
and then we offer 500.

24:04.811 --> 24:07.980
We are leaving each house
with a check on their table

24:08.114 --> 24:09.682
and a fucking signature
on our settlement.

24:09.849 --> 24:11.217
[Ainsley]
Hi, Rebecca.

24:14.687 --> 24:16.956
- Still spring-breaking?
- [Ainsley] Yeah.

24:17.089 --> 24:18.124
Are y'all working?

24:18.257 --> 24:19.191
We're almost done.

24:19.358 --> 24:20.493
Do you have a swimsuit?

24:20.627 --> 24:21.828
Not on me.

24:21.961 --> 24:23.863
Oh, well, you can borrow
one of mine.

24:24.864 --> 24:26.833
[chuckles softly]
Yeah, I've got a lot of work

24:26.966 --> 24:30.336
waiting for me
back at the hotel, so...

24:30.469 --> 24:31.804
- Right.
- Yeah. I'm sorry.

24:31.938 --> 24:33.039
Dang it.

24:33.205 --> 24:35.141
I know, right?

24:36.142 --> 24:37.744
Do y'all want some popcorn?

24:38.878 --> 24:39.879
Popcorn?

24:40.980 --> 24:44.216
Uh, no, I do not. Thank you.

24:44.383 --> 24:45.818
Nate?

24:45.952 --> 24:47.654
Oh, no, thanks.

24:47.787 --> 24:49.021
It's only 30 calories a cup.

24:49.188 --> 24:51.023
[chuckles]
Still. Thanks.

24:51.190 --> 24:53.025
Okay.

24:53.159 --> 24:56.128
- If you change your mind...
- Uh...

24:56.228 --> 24:57.564
[door opens]

24:59.832 --> 25:01.701
- [door closes]
- Are you kidding me?

25:01.834 --> 25:03.202
I know.

25:03.369 --> 25:05.237
The sexual harassment lawsuit's
literally writing itself.

25:05.371 --> 25:06.706
I have made that point.

25:06.839 --> 25:08.007
I will make it clearer.

25:08.140 --> 25:10.209
Nothing would please me more.

25:10.342 --> 25:13.145
- [truck beeping]
- Excuse me a moment.

25:23.322 --> 25:24.023
Can I help you?

25:24.156 --> 25:25.725
Got a delivery for Norris?

25:26.659 --> 25:27.960
All right.

25:28.060 --> 25:30.496
Mind if I take a look around
so we can make a game plan?

25:30.630 --> 25:32.031
A look around?

25:32.164 --> 25:33.165
The house.

25:33.265 --> 25:35.902
- You guys can come on in.
- Ah, hi.

25:36.068 --> 25:38.738
- Thank you.
- Mm.

25:38.871 --> 25:40.072
Hi.

25:41.874 --> 25:43.943
Uh, let's see...

25:44.110 --> 25:45.745
Don't worry. Mama put it all
on her credit card.

25:46.913 --> 25:48.180
Victor's credit card.

25:48.314 --> 25:50.683
- I don't know a Victor.
- My stepfather.

25:50.783 --> 25:54.587
Well, I guess he's
my ex-stepfather now.

25:56.055 --> 26:00.793
Writing itself, and expanding
its scope into fraud or larceny,

26:00.960 --> 26:04.163
depending how a prosecutor
chooses to approach this.

26:05.264 --> 26:07.967
Someone should have plausible
deniability over this disaster.

26:09.035 --> 26:11.270
Let's present this to
the families tomorrow morning.

26:11.437 --> 26:13.706
I'll set it up.
[sighs]

26:13.806 --> 26:16.242
[Angela] Great!
Can you guys please help me get

26:16.375 --> 26:18.410
all this old shit out of here
and bring all the new shit in?

26:18.544 --> 26:19.912
Okay?

26:20.046 --> 26:21.113
And I'll be upstairs
if you need anything,

26:21.280 --> 26:22.114
- all right?
- [mover] Yes, ma'am.

26:22.248 --> 26:23.783
Oh, hey, Ned.

26:23.916 --> 26:25.451
Nate.

26:25.584 --> 26:27.153
Hey, I say we just take

26:27.286 --> 26:29.088
everything out into the front
yard and unload the truck.

26:29.221 --> 26:30.422
Sounds good to me.

26:30.556 --> 26:32.324
Don't touch the files.

26:32.491 --> 26:33.693
- Got it?
- Got it.

26:35.962 --> 26:37.463
[grunting]

26:39.231 --> 26:40.466
Um...

26:42.735 --> 26:44.603
<i>["Something in the Orange"
by Zach Bryan playing]</i>

26:44.737 --> 26:47.640
<i>♪ I poisoned myself again ♪</i>

26:47.807 --> 26:50.276
<i>♪ Something in the orange
tells me... ♪</i>

26:50.409 --> 26:53.012
[woman] That is
my absolute favorite song.

26:53.179 --> 26:55.047
I'm Shelby.

26:55.147 --> 26:56.683
Ainsley Norris.

26:56.816 --> 26:59.218
From Aledo. I heard about you.

26:59.318 --> 27:01.453
Heard about me how?

27:01.587 --> 27:02.989
Well, the boys were all
drooling over you

27:03.155 --> 27:04.156
at the country club.

27:06.125 --> 27:09.095
Yeah, my mom sort of wore out
our welcome over there.

27:09.195 --> 27:10.930
I heard that, too.
[chuckles]

27:14.066 --> 27:16.168
Is your dad one of those
oil guys?

27:16.302 --> 27:17.670
Yeah, it's my spring break.

27:17.804 --> 27:19.772
And you're spending it
in Midland?

27:19.906 --> 27:22.809
Well, we were supposed
to go to Tulum,

27:22.942 --> 27:24.877
but a bunch of tourists
got killed,

27:25.011 --> 27:26.445
and our parents,
like, freaked out

27:26.578 --> 27:27.513
and canceled the whole thing.

27:27.646 --> 27:29.348
So lame.

27:29.481 --> 27:32.484
Well, there's a patch party
tomorrow night,

27:32.618 --> 27:34.586
- if you want to go.
- What's a patch party?

27:34.687 --> 27:38.157
We go out to the oil wells,
and bring kegs,

27:38.290 --> 27:40.426
and circle up the cars
on the pad and, I don't know,

27:40.526 --> 27:41.994
just dance and blow off
some steam.

27:43.029 --> 27:45.564
How fun. Um, yeah.

27:45.698 --> 27:47.166
Yeah, I'd love to go. What time?

27:47.299 --> 27:48.167
9 or so.

27:48.300 --> 27:49.668
Okay. Yeah, I'd love to go.

27:49.802 --> 27:51.037
Great. [chuckles]

27:51.170 --> 27:52.404
Well, I'll come over
and grab you.

27:52.571 --> 27:53.539
Okay.

27:53.706 --> 27:54.874
Thank you.

27:55.007 --> 27:55.942
Course.

27:56.042 --> 27:56.976
- Nice to meet you.
- Bye. You, too.

27:57.109 --> 28:00.479
<i>♪ Those headlights around ♪</i>

28:01.480 --> 28:03.249
<i>♪ atmospheric music ♪</i>

28:03.582 --> 28:05.785
<i>***</i>

28:18.230 --> 28:19.799
Goddamn it.

28:21.267 --> 28:24.436
This one just started
dropping off this past month.

28:25.872 --> 28:27.606
Goddamn it.

28:27.740 --> 28:29.776
Which crew maintains this field?

28:29.942 --> 28:31.177
Luis.

28:31.310 --> 28:32.979
Oh.

28:33.079 --> 28:35.782
These haven't
been reassigned yet.

28:37.583 --> 28:39.185
Hey, Boss, can we add
a little to your plate?

28:40.286 --> 28:41.587
Oh.
[sighs]

28:41.754 --> 28:43.923
This is a ways
from my turf, Tommy.

28:44.090 --> 28:46.625
I mean, ain't this part of that
co-op with Conoco over there?

28:46.793 --> 28:48.427
Can't they take this on?

28:48.560 --> 28:50.596
No, this ain't part
of the co-op.

28:52.398 --> 28:53.900
Well, here comes a crew now.

28:56.202 --> 28:57.804
Shit.

28:59.271 --> 29:01.774
Bud, that ain't a crew.

29:23.029 --> 29:24.463
Boss, you got anything with you?

29:24.596 --> 29:25.631
Oh, she stays on me.

29:26.665 --> 29:28.935
Listen, get pictures
of the license plates,

29:29.068 --> 29:30.269
and don't get caught
doing it, all right?

29:30.402 --> 29:31.703
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

29:38.978 --> 29:41.848
[vehicle doors closing]

29:50.823 --> 29:52.358
I been looking all over for you.

29:53.325 --> 29:54.726
Yeah? Well,
all you have to do is

29:54.827 --> 29:56.896
call the number
on the lease, Jimmy.

29:58.030 --> 30:00.666
You don't know me
to call me my first name.

30:02.168 --> 30:04.203
You call me fucking sir,
if you call me anything.

30:05.471 --> 30:07.373
You and me got
a real fucking problem.

30:07.539 --> 30:08.307
Yeah?

30:08.440 --> 30:11.177
Yeah. You owe me a lot of money.

30:11.310 --> 30:13.012
How's that?

30:13.145 --> 30:15.714
When all my product burned up
on the side of my road.

30:15.882 --> 30:17.049
Oh.
[laughs]

30:17.216 --> 30:18.417
Let me explain something
to you, all right?

30:19.451 --> 30:21.854
Number one,
it's our fucking road.

30:21.988 --> 30:24.991
It's part of the lease,
and we have deeded access to it.

30:25.124 --> 30:28.560
It's not your road
till the lease expires.

30:28.694 --> 30:30.963
All right? Number two,

30:31.063 --> 30:32.899
nowhere in this fucking lease
does it say

30:33.032 --> 30:35.001
that you can land
a fucking plane on it,

30:35.134 --> 30:36.502
and nowhere in this lease
does it say

30:36.635 --> 30:38.170
that you can use a plane of ours

30:38.304 --> 30:39.906
to truck your shit
into the country.

30:40.072 --> 30:42.841
Because of you,
I've got lawyers up my ass

30:42.975 --> 30:44.776
so far they can see
out of my mouth,

30:44.877 --> 30:48.514
not to mention the sheriff,
and the FAA and the NTSB.

30:48.647 --> 30:51.717
You just put a giant fucking
bull's-eye on this place.

30:52.851 --> 30:55.721
You owe me a lot of money.

30:55.854 --> 30:57.156
You know how much
that shit was worth?

30:57.289 --> 31:00.226
Do you know how much
this shit's worth?

31:00.392 --> 31:01.560
You're the one
with the problem, bud.

31:01.693 --> 31:03.062
I'm not the one
with the problem.

31:03.229 --> 31:05.932
See, the DEA has a satellite
above this fucking field now

31:06.065 --> 31:08.901
just waiting to see what kind
of stupid shit you pull next.

31:09.068 --> 31:11.570
And then you coming out here,
trying to shake me down

31:11.703 --> 31:14.306
has zero effect
on the multibillion-dollar,

31:14.406 --> 31:17.009
multinational corporations that
own and run this shit.

31:17.109 --> 31:18.310
They don't care.

31:21.080 --> 31:23.115
See, this is why
we didn't want you here.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.318
You know, I got a boss too,

31:26.418 --> 31:29.021
and he lost millions on my road.

31:29.888 --> 31:31.690
He wants it back.

31:31.790 --> 31:33.825
Maybe some of these wells
stop working.

31:35.094 --> 31:36.996
Maybe some of 'em start
blowing the fuck up.

31:38.064 --> 31:39.531
Bet they'll care then, huh?

31:39.665 --> 31:41.800
Oh, yeah, they will.

31:41.934 --> 31:44.570
They'll care so much
that the 1st Cavalry Division

31:44.703 --> 31:47.006
of the United States fucking
Army will come out here

31:47.106 --> 31:49.775
and start playing war games
inside a month.

31:51.110 --> 31:54.380
You don't know
who you're fucking with, Jimmy.

31:54.480 --> 31:57.649
So, why don't you just take
your licks, like a fucking man,

31:57.816 --> 31:59.785
and quit stealing planes
and landing 'em

31:59.918 --> 32:02.788
on fucking active
fucking roadways, all right?

32:02.921 --> 32:04.556
Matter of fact,
I got a good idea.

32:04.690 --> 32:05.724
How's this?

32:05.857 --> 32:07.926
How about you buy
your own fucking plane,

32:08.060 --> 32:11.230
build your own fucking runway?
How 'bout that?

32:11.330 --> 32:13.132
Yeah, well, because then you
can trace the plane back to me,

32:13.265 --> 32:15.034
and you know where it lands.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.336
You stick to drilling wells.

32:18.337 --> 32:20.973
You don't know anything
about my business.

32:22.074 --> 32:24.010
But you're about to learn.

32:31.650 --> 32:35.487
- [vehicle doors closing]
- [engines start]

32:55.341 --> 32:57.843
DEA has a satellite
on our field?

32:58.010 --> 32:59.845
Hell no, Dale.
I made that shit up.

32:59.978 --> 33:01.480
[Boss]
That's a problem.

33:02.414 --> 33:04.850
That's a real
fucking problem, Tommy.

33:05.017 --> 33:07.253
I don't need my guys
coming out here,

33:07.353 --> 33:09.355
getting shot up
by no fucking cartel

33:09.488 --> 33:11.490
in the goddamn desert.

33:11.623 --> 33:13.292
- I'll figure something out.
- Oh, you better.

33:13.425 --> 33:14.926
Because none of us stepping foot

33:15.027 --> 33:16.728
on this field until you do.

33:16.895 --> 33:18.597
Goddamn it.

33:22.901 --> 33:24.536
Dale, did you get it?

33:24.670 --> 33:26.205
Filmed the whole fucking thing.

33:26.372 --> 33:28.074
- Excellent.
- [engine starts]

33:35.947 --> 33:38.450
[line ringing]

33:38.550 --> 33:40.586
[phone ringing]

33:43.989 --> 33:45.124
Yeah.

33:45.224 --> 33:46.658
Hey, Monty, we got a problem

33:46.758 --> 33:48.127
we got to talk about in person.

33:48.227 --> 33:49.561
I'm headed back
to Fort Worth now.

33:49.728 --> 33:51.930
All right, I'll come
see you tomorrow.

33:52.098 --> 33:54.566
Yeah, afternoon's better.
Just come by the house.

33:54.733 --> 33:56.702
Okay, I'll call you
when I get close.

34:04.443 --> 34:06.278
Let's get the fuck out of here.

34:07.746 --> 34:08.914
[sighs]

34:16.088 --> 34:17.489
[exhales]

34:29.601 --> 34:31.270
[exhales]

34:36.041 --> 34:37.409
[water running]

34:49.421 --> 34:50.656
[Ariana]
I'm sorry.

34:54.426 --> 34:55.394
I'm sorry.

34:57.229 --> 34:58.597
[water turns off]

34:58.730 --> 34:59.665
For what?

35:00.999 --> 35:03.735
For kissing you. [sighs]

35:03.869 --> 35:05.070
It's just...
the insult of it, you know?

35:05.204 --> 35:07.306
He does nothing to help,
which is fine--

35:07.439 --> 35:09.908
I don't ask him to-- then
he questions who does and why?

35:10.008 --> 35:12.077
I won't have it.

35:12.178 --> 35:13.312
No, I guess not.

35:13.445 --> 35:15.981
You want to know
something funny?

35:16.114 --> 35:17.683
Elvio didn't
even like that prick.

35:17.816 --> 35:19.518
[both chuckle]

35:22.921 --> 35:24.656
You know, I'm just here
because you're brave enough

35:24.790 --> 35:26.592
to ask for help
when you need it.

35:26.725 --> 35:29.561
And I'm happy to give it,
if it's any help at all.

35:31.930 --> 35:33.932
It helps.

35:34.032 --> 35:35.667
And I need it.

35:37.669 --> 35:40.806
Gonna be harder than I thought
to keep this heart young.

35:43.041 --> 35:45.444
Um, I can make dinner.

35:47.179 --> 35:49.448
Uh, dinner?
No, no, thank you, um...

35:49.548 --> 35:52.684
I'm having dinner with...
with my family.

35:55.120 --> 35:57.689
Oh. They live here?

35:57.823 --> 35:59.491
Father does.

35:59.625 --> 36:02.461
Uh, mother's in town for...

36:02.561 --> 36:04.796
reasons I can't explain.
[chuckles]

36:04.896 --> 36:06.898
This dinner's a "have to,"
not a "want to,"

36:07.065 --> 36:08.133
if you know what I mean.

36:08.267 --> 36:10.502
I used to know what you mean.

36:11.537 --> 36:13.439
Then they all died.

36:16.375 --> 36:18.444
Don't ever miss
a family dinner, Cooper.

36:19.645 --> 36:21.247
'Cause one of them
will be the last.

36:22.914 --> 36:24.716
Could even be this one.

36:28.053 --> 36:29.855
Thank you for coming.

36:30.889 --> 36:33.725
Yeah, um, I'll find out
about the 401(k).

36:38.397 --> 36:40.266
You know what's
different about you?

36:43.402 --> 36:47.406
My... my friends give me
all this advice.

36:48.206 --> 36:50.642
Get a job. Sell the house.

36:50.742 --> 36:52.711
Move home.

36:52.844 --> 36:54.212
Find a man.

36:55.213 --> 36:57.416
Like I don't know the options.

37:00.586 --> 37:01.953
No advice from you.

37:06.392 --> 37:08.860
If I could think of something
to say that would help,

37:08.960 --> 37:10.161
I would say it.

37:11.497 --> 37:14.466
Nobody has something
to say that helps,

37:14.600 --> 37:16.167
but they keep talking.

37:18.937 --> 37:20.105
You listen.

37:26.044 --> 37:28.179
[sighs]

37:31.082 --> 37:32.818
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

37:33.151 --> 37:35.287
<i>***</i>

37:42.628 --> 37:44.630
<i>***</i>

38:00.812 --> 38:02.213
[grunts softly]

38:02.314 --> 38:05.183
[vehicle door opens, closes]

38:05.517 --> 38:07.453
<i>***</i>

38:25.337 --> 38:26.572
Hey.

38:29.441 --> 38:30.476
Hi, Daddy.

38:30.609 --> 38:32.378
Hey, honey.

38:32.544 --> 38:33.645
Nate.

38:35.681 --> 38:37.082
I'm gonna go, um-- yeah.

38:37.182 --> 38:38.550
[Tommy]
Yeah, all right.

38:43.054 --> 38:44.623
[keys jingle]

38:51.096 --> 38:53.031
Has this wall always been red?

38:53.198 --> 38:55.166
[chuckling]
No.

38:55.300 --> 38:57.102
I didn't think so.

39:01.707 --> 39:03.775
<i>[classical music
playing on stereo]</i>

39:05.377 --> 39:08.614
What in the fuck
is going on here?

39:15.754 --> 39:17.288
Honey?

39:18.256 --> 39:19.758
Here we go.

39:20.859 --> 39:21.760
Angela.

39:21.927 --> 39:23.662
You said 7, remember?

39:23.795 --> 39:26.398
No, you said 7,
I said I had to work.

39:26.532 --> 39:28.066
- You said you'd try.
- What's all this shit?

39:28.233 --> 39:30.436
- I did try.
- And you failed.

39:30.569 --> 39:32.438
What in the fuck
is all this stuff here?

39:32.571 --> 39:35.474
[laughs] Oh, I just steered into
the West Texas of it, right?

39:35.574 --> 39:36.575
I mean, we're here.

39:36.708 --> 39:37.509
There's no point
in decorating this place

39:37.643 --> 39:38.744
like a condo in Dallas.

39:38.877 --> 39:41.179
Well, where's the furniture
that was in here?

39:41.279 --> 39:42.914
I gave it to the movers.

39:43.081 --> 39:45.250
It don't belong to us.
We rent it.

39:45.383 --> 39:47.586
Well, this is
your furniture now.

39:47.719 --> 39:51.089
From a legal standpoint, no.
This would be...?

39:51.222 --> 39:54.125
- Victor's.
- Victor's furniture, yes.

39:55.226 --> 39:56.762
Charged it to
your husband, did you?

39:56.928 --> 39:59.631
He hasn't checked a credit card
bill in decades, honey.

39:59.798 --> 40:00.766
Well, he don't have to.

40:00.899 --> 40:02.167
That's what his accountant
is for.

40:02.267 --> 40:05.070
- Well, he doesn't either.
- [knocking at door]

40:07.405 --> 40:10.609
[laughs, squeals]

40:18.917 --> 40:21.520
[Angela whimpers] Aw.

40:22.454 --> 40:25.190
Hey, baby, come here.

40:25.290 --> 40:28.760
Oh, my God, you're so skinny.

40:28.894 --> 40:30.428
God, you're filthy.

40:30.562 --> 40:31.597
Have you been playing football?

40:31.730 --> 40:33.999
I-I was helping
a friend mow the lawn.

40:34.165 --> 40:36.167
Mm. Well...

40:36.334 --> 40:37.435
God, wash your hands.

40:37.569 --> 40:39.237
Oh, babe, take your boots off.

40:39.370 --> 40:41.206
And do we have time
for Cooper to take a shower?

40:41.306 --> 40:43.308
Hell, it's your show, honey.

40:43.441 --> 40:45.944
I'm not gonna take a shower.

40:46.077 --> 40:47.546
Okay.

40:48.514 --> 40:50.549
Here, come sit
next to your sister.

40:57.355 --> 40:59.691
You smell like the beach.

40:59.858 --> 41:01.326
You smell like a goat.

41:02.661 --> 41:04.663
- I'll see y'all after a while.
- Sit.

41:04.830 --> 41:06.397
Okay.

41:10.268 --> 41:12.103
[clears throat]

41:19.344 --> 41:22.113
[exhales] Okay.

41:25.116 --> 41:26.518
[sighs]

41:34.492 --> 41:35.561
Mm.

41:50.341 --> 41:54.079
My whole family together
for the first time in...

41:54.212 --> 41:56.582
it's been ten years.

41:59.484 --> 42:01.386
Sorry. I'm just
so fucking happy.

42:01.519 --> 42:04.590
[gasps] Should we bless it?

42:05.591 --> 42:08.794
Why not? I can use anything
I can get today.

42:09.761 --> 42:11.763
Grab hands.

42:15.233 --> 42:17.402
[clears throat]

42:17.535 --> 42:18.637
[exasperated sigh]

42:19.838 --> 42:21.072
I couldn't care less.

42:22.240 --> 42:23.842
God cares.

42:23.975 --> 42:25.877
- Ainsley, hold hands.
- [scoffs]

42:27.078 --> 42:28.814
So gross.

42:32.918 --> 42:35.020
[exhales]

42:36.054 --> 42:37.856
Lord, thank you for this day

42:37.956 --> 42:40.992
and thank you for bringing
my family back together.

42:41.092 --> 42:44.062
And thank you
for Dale and Neal--

42:44.195 --> 42:45.163
- Nathan. Nate.
- [laughs]

42:45.263 --> 42:46.431
[Angela]
Oh, shit.

42:46.564 --> 42:49.534
Sorry, Nathan. Nathan, God.

42:49.635 --> 42:50.702
Course you know his name

42:50.836 --> 42:52.638
'cause you're God,
but I didn't know it.

42:52.771 --> 42:54.773
I know it now.

42:54.906 --> 42:56.474
[sighs]

42:56.642 --> 42:59.210
Thank you for this food--

42:59.344 --> 43:02.547
which looks damn good,
if I do say so myself--

43:02.681 --> 43:04.115
I found a butcher
that imports wild boar

43:04.282 --> 43:06.517
from Italy,
if you can believe it.

43:06.618 --> 43:08.987
If you're gonna make a
Bolognese, it is by far the best

43:09.120 --> 43:11.022
to use wild boar
and not just ground pork.

43:11.122 --> 43:12.157
We still praying?

43:12.323 --> 43:14.626
I'm not sure. Maybe she forgot.

43:14.760 --> 43:16.962
[Angela] Help us to be mindful
of those less fortunate.

43:17.128 --> 43:21.532
Help us to celebrate you
by living our very best life.

43:22.400 --> 43:24.502
- Amen.
- [Ainsley] Amen.

43:24.670 --> 43:26.237
- [Dale and Nathan] Amen.
- Amen.

43:27.305 --> 43:29.207
Let's eat. [laughs]

43:29.307 --> 43:32.010
First time I've heard
blasphemy in a prayer.

43:32.177 --> 43:34.612
[Angela]
Pass me the wine.

43:34.746 --> 43:36.081
Okay.

43:36.214 --> 43:39.017
So, the food is Italian

43:39.150 --> 43:40.952
- and the wine is French.
- Mm.

43:41.086 --> 43:44.522
This is a Pomerol
from the Bordeaux region.

43:44.690 --> 43:46.825
It's a little wine-making
commune, isn't that cute?

43:46.958 --> 43:48.860
I'm gonna grab a beer.
Dale, you want one?

43:48.994 --> 43:49.995
- Thanks.
- All right.

43:50.128 --> 43:51.229
Beer?

43:51.329 --> 43:52.831
I can't drink wine.

43:52.964 --> 43:54.666
How come you can't drink wine?

43:54.800 --> 43:56.768
Because I'm an alcoholic.

43:56.902 --> 43:59.337
When did they stop fermenting
beer, Mr. Alcoholic?

43:59.470 --> 44:01.206
It's low-alcohol beer.

44:01.339 --> 44:03.008
If they start making
low-alcohol wine,

44:03.141 --> 44:05.043
I'll drink the shit out of it.

44:05.210 --> 44:06.411
You're no fun.

44:08.013 --> 44:09.848
Thank you.

44:09.981 --> 44:11.282
[clears throat]

44:11.416 --> 44:12.918
[blows nose]

44:16.587 --> 44:18.690
[coughs, clears throat]

44:18.824 --> 44:20.191
Mmm.

44:20.358 --> 44:21.727
Here you go, bud.

44:24.029 --> 44:25.764
[Angela clears throat]

44:29.034 --> 44:31.937
[sighs] Are you all better
from your explosion, honey?

44:33.304 --> 44:34.372
I'm fine.

44:35.741 --> 44:38.043
You know,
your sister's following

44:38.176 --> 44:41.146
in your footsteps, baby.
She's going to Tech.

44:41.279 --> 44:44.015
I'm sure all the sororities
are beside themselves with joy.

44:44.149 --> 44:45.550
Cooper, be nice.

44:45.717 --> 44:47.585
Or maybe just don't speak.

44:47.753 --> 44:48.553
For the rest of your life.

44:48.720 --> 44:50.555
[Tommy]
So, uh...

44:52.357 --> 44:54.225
What'd you say this stuff is?

44:54.392 --> 44:55.894
Bolognese.

44:56.061 --> 44:59.865
It's three types of meat--
veal, beef, and wild boar--

44:59.998 --> 45:01.499
- like I was telling God.
- [Dale] Mm.

45:01.632 --> 45:02.734
So, spaghetti.

45:02.868 --> 45:05.570
Not spaghetti. No.

45:05.703 --> 45:07.405
Spaghetti doesn't use
veal or pork

45:07.538 --> 45:10.508
and it doesn't use cream
and it doesn't use sugar.

45:10.608 --> 45:11.542
Is there sugar in this?

45:11.676 --> 45:14.012
Not enough to make a difference.

45:38.369 --> 45:39.838
[sighs]
How was your day, Nathan?

45:41.239 --> 45:42.107
My day?

45:42.240 --> 45:43.208
Mm-hmm.

45:43.308 --> 45:45.476
[laughs]

45:45.610 --> 45:47.212
Uh, I'm an attorney.

45:47.312 --> 45:48.713
Oh?

45:48.814 --> 45:50.816
Well, I can't...

45:50.982 --> 45:53.684
My day is governed
by attorney-client privilege.

45:53.785 --> 45:55.486
So you can't talk
about your day?

45:55.620 --> 45:57.122
No, ma'am.

45:57.288 --> 45:58.756
Mm-hmm.

46:00.892 --> 46:02.393
Dale.

46:02.527 --> 46:03.962
How was yours?

46:06.464 --> 46:08.033
'Bout a five, don't you think?

46:08.133 --> 46:10.235
Well, till the end of the day,
it was just about a two.

46:10.335 --> 46:12.303
What happened?

46:20.578 --> 46:22.747
You a fucking lawyer now, too?

46:22.881 --> 46:25.183
You want to hear about my day?

46:25.316 --> 46:27.118
All right, here it is.

46:27.252 --> 46:29.254
I stood out in
a hundred-degree heat all day

46:29.387 --> 46:32.057
staring at gauges
on fucking oil pumps,

46:32.157 --> 46:33.892
until some cartel members
showed up

46:33.992 --> 46:35.894
and demanded we pay 'em back

46:35.994 --> 46:38.796
for the drugs they lost
on our lease

46:38.930 --> 46:41.566
to the tune of about
$30 million dollars.

46:42.633 --> 46:44.669
Guess how they took it
when I said no.

46:45.871 --> 46:47.939
- That really happened?
- Yeah.

46:48.039 --> 46:49.507
Yeah. Yeah, it really happened.

46:49.640 --> 46:50.976
Does Monty know?

46:51.109 --> 46:52.377
I'm going over there tomorrow.

46:52.543 --> 46:54.745
<i>[opera music playing]</i>

46:55.013 --> 46:57.082
<i>***</i>

47:03.321 --> 47:05.190
Well, let's see. What else?

47:08.860 --> 47:10.328
My hemorrhoid finally burst.

47:10.461 --> 47:12.130
[groans]

47:12.230 --> 47:14.866
It's amazing how 80 miles
of dirt road will

47:15.000 --> 47:17.002
work through
one of those pesky ones.

47:26.544 --> 47:28.213
Excuse me.

47:35.753 --> 47:37.055
[dishes clatter]

47:40.758 --> 47:42.093
Dad.

47:43.561 --> 47:44.362
What?

47:44.495 --> 47:46.965
Go talk to her. Say sorry.

47:47.865 --> 47:49.234
All right.

47:49.367 --> 47:50.902
[Ainsley]
Be nice.

47:54.339 --> 47:56.507
You don't think we're
doing this every night, do you?

47:56.641 --> 48:00.411
I don't know, but this fucking
spaghetti's pretty good, though.

48:05.150 --> 48:07.652
Didn't take you long
to ruin that dinner.

48:09.320 --> 48:10.888
[pot bangs against trash can]

48:11.022 --> 48:13.324
I spent all day

48:13.424 --> 48:17.028
shopping and decorating
and cooking for you.

48:17.162 --> 48:19.430
That's your three
favorite things to do, so

48:19.564 --> 48:22.233
I'm glad you did 'em, honey,
but if we have

48:22.367 --> 48:24.802
a mouse fart's chance in hell
of making this work,

48:24.936 --> 48:26.271
you got to remember
why we're here.

48:26.437 --> 48:28.073
[groans]

48:28.206 --> 48:30.108
We're here to work.

48:30.241 --> 48:31.909
Midland's not home to any of us.

48:32.043 --> 48:33.945
How long have you
been here, Tommy?

48:34.079 --> 48:35.346
Hmm?

48:36.881 --> 48:38.549
You know, let me answer for you.

48:38.683 --> 48:40.118
Thirty-three years.

48:41.152 --> 48:43.121
You may not like your home,
but this is it.

48:44.189 --> 48:47.392
And I need this to feel like
a home, if we're gonna be in it.

48:47.525 --> 48:51.229
All right, well, if you want
to put a hundred grand

48:51.329 --> 48:53.064
on your husband's credit card
to spruce the place up--

48:53.164 --> 48:54.465
Two hundred and twenty.

48:54.632 --> 48:56.767
Okay. Well, do it for you.

48:56.901 --> 48:59.270
Do it 'cause you like it.
You know, don't do it for us,

48:59.404 --> 49:01.839
and don't expect us
to appreciate it, or even care.

49:01.973 --> 49:04.409
I mean, if you want to cook,
be my guest,

49:04.509 --> 49:07.012
but don't expect us
to be here when it's ready.

49:07.145 --> 49:08.946
And don't expect us
to appreciate it.

49:09.080 --> 49:10.481
I mean, we do,

49:10.615 --> 49:12.483
but don't expect it.
See, that's the problem.

49:12.650 --> 49:14.819
You got this image in your brain

49:14.986 --> 49:16.421
of how everything's
supposed to go,

49:16.554 --> 49:20.858
but we don't know what that is,
you know? We don't see it.

49:20.992 --> 49:24.262
So, when it don't go the way
you dreamed it up,

49:24.362 --> 49:26.297
you get pissed off,
you throw a tantrum,

49:26.431 --> 49:29.167
and then I get pissed off,
throw a bigger tantrum,

49:29.300 --> 49:31.136
and then we're back
to square one.

49:33.971 --> 49:35.173
[sighs]

49:35.306 --> 49:37.275
Our children hate each other.

49:37.375 --> 49:38.343
Honey, they're teenagers.

49:38.509 --> 49:39.710
They're supposed to
hate each other.

49:39.844 --> 49:42.547
Cooper is not a teenager.

49:42.713 --> 49:44.182
He's a man.

49:44.315 --> 49:47.185
I mean, a man.
When the fuck did that happen?

49:48.653 --> 49:50.955
I mean, do I look like a woman

49:51.089 --> 49:53.224
with a 22-year-old?

49:54.892 --> 49:57.195
I'm turning into a GMILF.

49:57.328 --> 49:58.896
The hell's a GMILF?

49:59.030 --> 50:00.898
A grandmother I'd like to fuck.

50:01.032 --> 50:03.000
I'm aging out of cougar,
for fuck's sake.

50:03.134 --> 50:04.269
All right, well, listen, honey.

50:04.369 --> 50:06.304
Uh, let me ask you a question,
and when I do,

50:06.404 --> 50:07.438
please don't hit me, all right?

50:07.538 --> 50:09.440
What?

50:09.540 --> 50:12.510
At what point are we
in your menstrual cycle?

50:14.412 --> 50:16.013
Oh, you motherfucker,
don't you dare.

50:16.147 --> 50:17.148
Well, let me guess.

50:17.282 --> 50:19.184
I'm gonna say
right towards the end.

50:19.317 --> 50:21.086
You need to be real careful.

50:21.252 --> 50:22.220
Am I wrong?

50:22.387 --> 50:23.488
I am stone-ass serious
right now.

50:23.588 --> 50:25.390
Tell me the fucking truth,
am I wrong?

50:26.457 --> 50:27.925
[laughs] It's coming any minute.

50:28.093 --> 50:28.993
That's what I figured.

50:29.094 --> 50:31.196
[chuckles] I need a Midol

50:31.329 --> 50:32.830
and a fucking margarita.

50:32.963 --> 50:35.066
Well, here's the good news,
we got all of that.

50:35.200 --> 50:36.434
- [crying]
- Come here, honey.

50:36.567 --> 50:37.568
Come here.

50:39.570 --> 50:41.972
[sniffles]

50:42.073 --> 50:43.074
[sighs]

50:43.208 --> 50:44.542
You just cry it all out,

50:44.675 --> 50:47.078
and then we'll go finish the
spaghetti before it gets cold,

50:47.212 --> 50:49.247
all right?

50:49.414 --> 50:51.316
Call it spaghetti again
and see what happens.

50:54.919 --> 50:56.254
Spaghetti.

50:56.421 --> 50:59.657
God, you just couldn't
help yourself, could you?

51:01.626 --> 51:03.228
Oh!

51:03.361 --> 51:04.595
- You like that?
- No.

51:04.762 --> 51:06.364
- I don't like that.
- Mm.

51:06.497 --> 51:08.466
Why in the hell do you think
I would like that?

51:08.633 --> 51:09.367
[laughs]

51:09.500 --> 51:10.735
[Angela]
You're fine.

51:10.868 --> 51:14.172
This is an unsustainable way
for us all to cohabitate.

51:14.272 --> 51:16.107
It's got a shelf life,
that's for sure.

51:16.274 --> 51:18.543
[Angela laughing]

51:20.811 --> 51:22.147
What're you smiling for?

51:23.148 --> 51:25.316
Why aren't you?

51:25.450 --> 51:27.051
That's the question.

51:28.085 --> 51:28.819
'Cause I'm old enough
to remember

51:28.953 --> 51:29.820
when they were together.

51:29.987 --> 51:31.989
[Angela laughing]

51:32.157 --> 51:34.659
<i>[opera music continues]</i>

51:41.899 --> 51:44.369
<i>♪ slow, somber music ♪</i>

51:44.635 --> 51:46.637
<i>***</i>

51:53.444 --> 51:55.380
[phone buzzing]

52:02.987 --> 52:04.155
You okay?

52:04.289 --> 52:05.990
[shuddering]
I'm really scared.

52:06.157 --> 52:07.925
Scared of what?

52:08.025 --> 52:10.195
Every car that drives by.

52:10.328 --> 52:12.830
Every creak this house makes.
I... [sniffles]

52:14.232 --> 52:16.934
I don't know how
to do this by myself.

52:17.034 --> 52:19.103
I just don't know how to do it.

52:19.204 --> 52:22.173
[sniffles] I'm too scared
to even miss him.

52:22.340 --> 52:24.975
You got that big dog
by you, yeah?

52:25.109 --> 52:27.278
Yeah, he's on the bed.

52:27.378 --> 52:29.046
Well, there's not
a boogeyman in the world

52:29.214 --> 52:30.515
that wants to mess
with that dog.

52:30.648 --> 52:32.850
That's why Elvio got him.

52:33.017 --> 52:34.919
To watch over us
while he was working.

52:35.019 --> 52:36.354
<i>He chose well.</i>

52:36.487 --> 52:38.456
You've got plenty of things
to worry about,

52:38.589 --> 52:40.791
but someone coming in that house
is not one of them.

52:42.660 --> 52:44.395
Yeah, I guess you're right.

52:45.863 --> 52:47.031
Sorry for calling so late.

52:47.198 --> 52:49.434
You call anytime.

52:53.671 --> 52:54.872
Good night.

52:59.477 --> 53:01.212
[sniffles]

53:08.919 --> 53:10.788
<i>***</i>

53:24.735 --> 53:26.737
<i>***</i>

53:47.057 --> 53:49.059
Out late, huh?

53:50.595 --> 53:52.430
Get this motherfucker.
Get this motherfucker.

53:52.597 --> 53:56.401
[grunting]

53:56.534 --> 53:58.636
[objects crashing]

54:02.973 --> 54:05.142
<i>***</i>

54:31.336 --> 54:33.471
<i>***</i>

54:44.615 --> 54:46.083
[sighs softly]

54:54.825 --> 54:57.161
[sighs]

55:00.831 --> 55:02.600
[exhales]
Mm.

55:22.319 --> 55:25.122
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

55:25.255 --> 55:27.224
I didn't mean to wake you up.

55:27.392 --> 55:28.926
It's an early one, huh?

55:29.026 --> 55:31.195
Yeah, I got to go to Fort Worth.

55:32.863 --> 55:34.399
When are you back?

55:35.232 --> 55:36.867
When your period's over.

55:38.335 --> 55:39.604
Watch it.

55:40.638 --> 55:43.541
No, late tonight
or in the morning.

55:43.674 --> 55:45.776
You want me to bring you
something back from up there?

55:45.876 --> 55:47.612
[sighs]

55:47.712 --> 55:49.680
I should go, too.

55:51.248 --> 55:54.218
I need to sit down with Victor.

55:56.120 --> 56:00.024
Honey, I think he's probably
got it all figured out by now.

56:01.225 --> 56:03.360
I mean, he was good to me.

56:03.494 --> 56:05.596
- Yeah.
- And he was good to our kids.

56:06.864 --> 56:08.566
He deserves a face-to-face.

56:08.733 --> 56:10.701
Yeah, well, I know
you think about it that way,

56:10.835 --> 56:15.039
but from a man's perspective,
I'd rather you just call me.

56:15.172 --> 56:16.340
That way you're not sitting
around the living room,

56:16.441 --> 56:18.375
- all awkward and stuff.
- Mm-hmm.

56:18.509 --> 56:22.547
Doing some weird handshake
or half a hug.

56:23.614 --> 56:25.416
Now, if you need
to do it for you,

56:25.583 --> 56:28.453
then I get it,
that's another thing.

56:28.619 --> 56:30.354
Well, I do.

56:30.488 --> 56:32.256
'Cause this feels like cheating.

56:32.423 --> 56:34.358
Well, hell,
it is cheating, honey.

56:34.492 --> 56:37.027
- It's been cheating.
- [groans]

56:37.161 --> 56:39.597
Going to Fort Worth is
not gonna change anything.

56:39.764 --> 56:41.065
Especially for him.

56:43.801 --> 56:45.603
He has my car.

56:46.637 --> 56:48.506
[laughs] Okay,
now we're getting somewhere.

56:50.441 --> 56:51.942
Can I ride with you?

56:53.077 --> 56:55.646
You can do anything you want to.

56:56.647 --> 56:58.516
- [chuckles softly]
- [keys jingle]

57:01.085 --> 57:02.820
[sighs]

57:09.026 --> 57:11.462
Last chance to back out
if you don't want this.

57:14.999 --> 57:17.535
If you don't think
we can make this work.

57:20.871 --> 57:23.307
I don't think we have
an ice cube's chance in hell

57:23.440 --> 57:25.643
to make this work.

57:28.479 --> 57:32.550
But I don't possess the power
to say no to you.

57:36.487 --> 57:39.824
Especially when you look
at me like that.

57:46.897 --> 57:50.034
[sighs] You are so close
to being trained.

57:50.200 --> 57:53.070
[laughs]
Is that right?

57:53.170 --> 57:55.239
[laughs, sighs]

57:56.306 --> 57:58.543
Get dressed.
I'll meet you downstairs.

58:00.878 --> 58:03.347
<i>***</i>

58:17.327 --> 58:18.929
<i>[rap music playing over stereo]</i>

58:21.331 --> 58:23.534
Hey, you all know
where this fool is?

58:26.203 --> 58:27.504
<i>♪ There's a lot at stake ♪</i>

58:27.638 --> 58:29.473
<i>♪ So you know I'm A-1 ♪</i>

58:29.607 --> 58:30.708
<i>♪ This is my time ♪</i>

58:30.841 --> 58:32.209
<i>♪ Gotta climb up... ♪</i>

58:32.342 --> 58:33.510
Just leave him.

58:33.644 --> 58:35.412
<i>♪ Before my time's up ♪</i>

58:35.546 --> 58:37.882
<i>♪ I know that feeling,
that could never stop me ♪</i>

58:38.015 --> 58:39.650
<i>♪ I gotta grind now ♪</i>

58:39.750 --> 58:41.285
<i>♪ They could never copy... ♪</i>

58:53.564 --> 58:55.432
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

58:55.766 --> 58:57.635
<i>***</i>

59:19.156 --> 59:21.091
[Angela]
<i>Whoo! I mean, let's go!</i>

59:21.225 --> 59:23.460
[laughs]

59:23.628 --> 59:26.196
[groans]
This is gonna be fun.

59:26.330 --> 59:28.766
- This is like a road trip.
- It is a road trip.

59:28.899 --> 59:30.434
That's what they mean
when they say road trip,

59:30.567 --> 59:31.669
what we're doing right now.

59:31.769 --> 59:34.605
Grumpy without coffee. Here.

59:34.772 --> 59:36.440
Not right now.
I'll get to it later.

59:36.573 --> 59:38.542
We should play
one of those games

59:38.643 --> 59:40.277
where every time you see

59:40.444 --> 59:42.112
an out-of-state license plate
you get a point,

59:42.279 --> 59:45.282
and when you see a car
with only one headlight working

59:45.449 --> 59:46.550
you get five points.

59:46.651 --> 59:48.152
How do we know they only
got one headlight?

59:48.318 --> 59:49.386
It's daytime.

59:49.486 --> 59:50.688
Nobody's got
their fucking headlights on.

59:50.788 --> 59:52.589
What happened to your inability
to say no to me,

59:52.723 --> 59:54.324
you stick
in the motherfucking mud?

59:55.325 --> 59:57.094
I can't do this for four hours.

59:57.227 --> 59:58.863
- [scoffs]
- [phone buzzing]

01:00:00.397 --> 01:00:01.732
Yeah.

01:00:01.832 --> 01:00:02.933
[Rick over phone]
<i>Hey, you need to come</i>

01:00:03.067 --> 01:00:04.334
<i>see the mess
they made over here.</i>

01:00:04.468 --> 01:00:06.070
They got all my pipes
stacked together.

01:00:06.203 --> 01:00:09.439
Six-inch, eight-inch, ten-inch
bundled like fucking T-posts.

01:00:09.573 --> 01:00:11.809
They should've come
on separate trucks.

01:00:11.942 --> 01:00:14.311
Yeah, they should've done
a lot of shit they didn't do.

01:00:14.444 --> 01:00:15.846
I'm gonna need a Cat
with a magnet over here

01:00:15.980 --> 01:00:17.081
to sort this shit out.

01:00:17.214 --> 01:00:18.482
Well, I'm about ten minutes
from you.

01:00:18.615 --> 01:00:20.084
I'll be right there, all right?

01:00:21.385 --> 01:00:23.353
We got to take
a little detour, honey.

01:00:25.322 --> 01:00:26.957
I'm gonna get to see you work?

01:00:28.358 --> 01:00:29.559
That's so hot.

01:00:29.660 --> 01:00:31.595
You gonna yell at anybody?

01:00:32.496 --> 01:00:33.731
Yeah, probably.

01:00:34.765 --> 01:00:36.901
You want me to give you
a hand job?

01:00:37.835 --> 01:00:39.403
[laughs]

01:01:11.135 --> 01:01:14.338
Sweetheart, you got to stay
in the truck.

01:01:14.471 --> 01:01:15.706
Stay here?

01:01:15.873 --> 01:01:18.042
Yeah. There's cranes
and excavators

01:01:18.208 --> 01:01:19.877
and front-end loaders
moving shit everywhere.

01:01:20.044 --> 01:01:21.846
You got to have a hard hat
and steel-toe boots.

01:01:22.713 --> 01:01:24.982
Well, are your boots steel-toed?

01:01:25.082 --> 01:01:27.117
[chuckling]
Don't you look at me that way.

01:01:27.217 --> 01:01:29.720
[laughs]

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:32.890
You're bringing
that hard hat home.

01:01:34.224 --> 01:01:36.426
[laughs]
My God.

01:01:38.863 --> 01:01:40.530
You see this shit?

01:01:40.664 --> 01:01:42.767
It's gonna take me two
fucking days to sort this out.

01:01:42.933 --> 01:01:44.601
Yeah, well, that's faster
than they can.

01:01:44.769 --> 01:01:46.303
I shouldn't have
to do it at all.

01:01:46.403 --> 01:01:47.805
It's a waste of my fucking time.

01:01:51.575 --> 01:01:53.944
- Someone move those pipes!
- No, no, no, no, no.

01:01:54.111 --> 01:01:55.012
Do not move the pipes.

01:01:55.112 --> 01:01:56.246
He'll bleed out.
Don't touch him.

01:01:56.380 --> 01:01:57.547
[man]
We need a Med Sled out here!

01:01:57.681 --> 01:01:58.415
[Tommy]
Hey, buddy...

01:01:58.548 --> 01:02:00.117
[panting]

01:02:00.284 --> 01:02:01.451
- Hey, Rick.
- [grunts]

01:02:01.618 --> 01:02:03.253
Hang in there, buddy.

01:02:03.420 --> 01:02:05.756
You just breathe slow.
Don't get all excited.

01:02:05.923 --> 01:02:07.591
- All right?
- I want to call my wife.

01:02:07.758 --> 01:02:09.894
I-I don't have my phone.
I don't have my phone.

01:02:10.027 --> 01:02:10.861
Okay, here. Here.

01:02:10.995 --> 01:02:12.396
Okay. There you go.

01:02:12.529 --> 01:02:14.664
Listen, we're gonna get you
some help, all right?

01:02:16.901 --> 01:02:18.402
[Rick]
Wait, wait, wait. Hey. Hey.

01:02:18.535 --> 01:02:20.637
[panting]

01:02:20.771 --> 01:02:22.372
What do I, what do I tell her?

01:02:25.275 --> 01:02:26.977
Tell her you love her.

01:02:27.744 --> 01:02:29.279
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

01:02:35.619 --> 01:02:38.288
Pick up. Pick up.
Pick up. Pick up.

01:02:42.592 --> 01:02:44.094
- Give me your phone.
- What's wrong?

01:02:44.228 --> 01:02:45.429
Honey, just give me your phone.

01:02:45.562 --> 01:02:47.031
- What happened?
- And stay in the truck, please.

01:02:50.167 --> 01:02:51.301
[line ringing]

01:02:51.435 --> 01:02:53.470
[dispatcher]
<i>911, what's your emergency?</i>

01:02:53.637 --> 01:02:55.505
Yes, I'm at a drilling rig

01:02:55.672 --> 01:02:57.407
off of Country Road 137.

01:02:57.507 --> 01:02:59.209
I'm gonna send you
GPS coordinates.

01:02:59.309 --> 01:03:02.446
I've got a white male,
in his 30s,

01:03:02.579 --> 01:03:04.014
and his body's been crushed.

01:03:04.148 --> 01:03:05.649
[dispatcher]
<i>How was it crushed, sir?</i>

01:03:05.782 --> 01:03:08.953
- Oil field pipe.
- [dispatcher] <i>Is he breathing?</i>

01:03:15.692 --> 01:03:17.261
[Tommy]
No, ma'am.

01:03:17.361 --> 01:03:19.496
[dispatcher] <i>Okay, do you or
anyone on the scene know CPR?</i>

01:03:19.629 --> 01:03:22.532
It's not possible
to give him CPR.

01:03:33.377 --> 01:03:36.346
<i>[singer vocalizing]</i>

01:03:46.690 --> 01:03:50.327
<i>***</i>

01:04:02.873 --> 01:04:04.408
<i>♪ atmospheric music ♪</i>

01:04:04.741 --> 01:04:06.911
<i>***</i>

01:04:34.771 --> 01:04:36.941
<i>***</i>

01:04:40.777 --> 01:04:43.813
<i>***</i>
